{"Category": "Social Justice, Diversity/Equity/Inclusion, History, Humanities, Leadership, School Design", "End Date": "", "Name": "\"The Urgency of Teacher Racial/Ethnic Diversity in an Increasingly Diverse Society\" - Presented by Travis Bristol '03", "URL": "https://www.amherst.edu/news/calendar/node/687878", "Location": "Amherst College, Amherst, MA", "Time": "8:00-9:00pm", "Date": "Fri, Nov 10, 2017", "Organization": "Amherst College", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "At the very moment policy-makers call for increasing the racial/ethnic diversity of the teaching force, teachers of color continue to leave the profession at higher rates than their white colleagues. This talk will highlight research that points to the \"added-value\" for students of color when taught by a teacher of color. Additionally, this talk will provide guidance for researchers, policy makers and practitioners looking to recruit, support and retain teachers of color.\n\nAmherst College alumnus Travis J. Bristol '03, a former high school English teacher and World Bank consultant, is an assistant professor in English education at Boston University School of Education with an affiliation in educational leadership and policy studies."},
