{"Category": "Humanities, Social Justice, Diversity/Equity/Inclusion, Literature, History", "End Date": "", "Name": "Black Masculinity and Race Traitors:  Examining Black Male Race Trators in 100 years of African American Literature", "URL": "https://www.umass.edu/wgss/event/masculinities-research-brown-bag-series", "Location": "Umass Amherst, Amherst, MA", "Time": "12:15 PM", "Date": "Wed, Nov 29, 2017", "Organization": "Umass Amherst", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "Greg Coleman, Doctoral Candidate in English\n\nPlease join us for this Masculinities Research Brown Bag series. Co-sponsored by WGSS and the UMass Men and Masculinities Center.  Our aim is to bring together members of our community who are doing research in some capacity about masculinities, as well as those interested in learning about this research, to share research, discuss methodological issues, trends, etc.  "},
