{"Category": "Health, Counseling, Diversity/Equity/Inclusion", "End Date": "", "Name": "Author Talk: John Elder Robison", "URL": "http://www.umass.edu/events/author-talk-john-elder-robison", "Location": "Umass Amherst, Amherst, MA", "Time": "5:00-7:00pm", "Date": "Thu, Nov 30, 2017", "Organization": "Umass Amherst", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "John Elder Robison\u2019s works include Be Different (2011), a how-to guide for grownups with autism; Raising Cubby (2013), the story of raising his autistic son; and Switched On (2016), about his participation as a research subject in brain studies.\n\nRobison is active in the autism civil rights movement and is a strong supporter of neurodiversity \u2013 the idea that autism and ADHD are a natural part of humanity, essential for our success, and should be honored and accepted even as we work to relieve any disability they may cause.   \n"},
