{"Category": "Arts", "End Date": "", "Name": "Gallery Talk with Alla Rosenfeld, European and Russian art curator", "URL": "https://www.amherst.edu/news/calendar/node/688476", "Location": "Mead Art Museum, Amherst, MA", "Time": "12:00-1:00pm", "Date": "Wed, Dec 6, 2017", "Organization": "Amherst College, Mead Art Museum", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "This talk is conjunction with the exhibition \"From the Picturesque to the Modern Vision: Landscape Painting in Europe Across the Centuries\". Take a break from your day to learn about the history of European landscape painting with Curator Alla Rosenfeld."},
{"Category": "Science, Sustainability, STEM", "End Date": "", "Name": "Air Source Heat Pumps \u2013 The Latest in Efficient Heating & Cooling", "URL": "http://www.hitchcockcenter.org/programs/community-programs/#sustainability", "Location": "Amherst, MA", "Time": "7:00-8:30pm", "Date": "Wed, Dec 6, 2017", "Organization": "Hitchcock Center for the Environment", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "An air source heat pump is a system which transfers heat from outside to inside a building, or vice versa. Air at any temperature above absolute zero contains some energy. An air-source heat pump transfers (\u2018pumps\u2019) some of this energy as heat from one place to another, for example between the outside and inside of a building. This can provide space heating or cooling. A single system can be designed to transfer heat in either direction, to heat or cool the interior of the building in winter and summer respectively."},
